<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Evaluate/Prevention</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">In most cases this warning is caused by an operator fault at the customer (entering the wrong media thickness). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In rare cases the Z-motion system or M&amp;C-scanner of the engine is broken. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-45E72CCA-32F0-41FD-ACF2-4A4D42D55C79" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Background info</b></title><p class="- topic/p ">The build up of a printed image is done is both directions of the carriage movement (Bi-Directional). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Bi-directional errors might be caused by an incorrect media thickness. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Therefore, the thickness of the media is determined as part of the media calibration. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The build up of a printed image is done is both directions of the carriage movement (Bi-Directional). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Bi-directional errors might be caused by an incorrect media thickness. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Therefore, the thickness of the media is determined as part of the media calibration. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The build up of a printed image is done is both directions of the carriage movement (Bi-Directional). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Bi-directional errors might be caused by an incorrect media thickness. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Therefore, the thickness of the media is determined as part of the media calibration. 
